$ LevelDB

LevelDB is a key-value storage library. Both, keys and values are arbitrary byte arrays.

The main operations provided by the library are:
  • `Put(key, value)`
  • `Get(key)`
  • `Delete(key)`

Multiple operations can be executed in one *atomic batch*.

Data is compressed using → https://research.google/pubs/pub27898/[Snappy].

LevelDB is implemented in a similar fashion like → https://research.google/pubs/pub27898/[BigTable tablet] (See section 5.3).

  

links:
  → https://github.com/google/leveldb[Github repo]
